        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1199426156" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12158529960621979023">A comprehensively argued case for cultural fluidity and “simplification” as a political response of state-evasion. This is enormously helpful in looking at history with fewer state-friendly assumptions, even if it can be a little overwhelming to a reader unfamiliar with Southeast Asia. It doesn&apos;t pretend to ring true today, but it&apos;s enlightening in creating more complete histories. So good. So good and so needed.</span>
  <span id="freeText12158529960621979023" style="display:none">A comprehensively argued case for cultural fluidity and “simplification” as a political response of state-evasion. This is enormously helpful in looking at history with fewer state-friendly assumptions, even if it can be a little overwhelming to a reader unfamiliar with Southeast Asia. It doesn't pretend to ring true today, but it's enlightening in creating more complete histories. So good. So good and so needed.</span>
